117 int32_t MmwaveLink_verifyReportCount(void)
118 {
119  uint32_t i, numRep;
120  int32_t retVal = 0;
121  char testname[64];
122  uint8_t reportMode;
123 
124  if(gTestMiscCfg.testAdvancedFrame == false)
125  {
126  numRep = frameCfg.numFrames / calMonTimeUnitConf.calibMonTimeUnit;
127  }
128  else
129  {
130  /*From ICD: One FTTI can have multiple frames in legacy frame configuration or in advanced frame configuration
131  - each frame can have multiple sub-frames and each sub-frame can have multiple bursts.*/
132  numRep = advFrameCfg.frameSeq.numFrames / calMonTimeUnitConf.calibMonTimeUnit;
133  }
134 
135  /* Check that for each enabled monitoring feature all reports have been received and
136  no reports were generated for the features that were not enabled.*/
137  for(i = 0; i < MMWAVELINK_TEST_MAX_NUM_MON; i++)
138  {
139  switch(i)
140  {
141  case 0:
142  sprintf(&testname[0], "MON_TEMP");
143  reportMode = tempMonCfg.reportMode;
144  break;
145  case 1:
146  sprintf(&testname[0],"MON_RX_GAIN_PH ");
147  reportMode = rxGainPhaseMonCfg.reportMode;
148  break;
149  case 2:
150  sprintf(&testname[0],"MON_RX_NOISE_FIG ");
151  reportMode = rxNoiseMonCfg.reportMode;
152  break;
153  case 3:
154  sprintf(&testname[0],"MON_RX_IF_STAGE ");
155  reportMode = monRxIfStageCfg.reportMode;
156  break;
157  case 4:
158  sprintf(&testname[0],"MON_TX0_POWER ");
159  reportMode = tx0PowMonCfg.reportMode;
160  break;
161  case 5:
162  sprintf(&testname[0],"MON_TX1_POWER ");
163  reportMode = tx1PowMonCfg.reportMode;
164  break;
165  case 6:
166  sprintf(&testname[0],"MON_TX2_POWER ");
167  reportMode = tx2PowMonCfg.reportMode;
168  break;
169  case 7:
170  sprintf(&testname[0],"MON_TX0_BALL_BRK ");
171  reportMode = tx0BallBreakMonCfg.reportMode;
172  break;
173  case 8:
174  sprintf(&testname[0],"MON_TX1_BALL_BRK ");
175  reportMode = tx1BallBreakMonCfg.reportMode;
176  break;
177  case 9:
178  sprintf(&testname[0],"MON_TX2_BALL_BRK ");
179  reportMode = tx2BallBreakMonCfg.reportMode;
180  break;
181  case 10:
182  sprintf(&testname[0],"MON_TX_GAIN_PHASE ");
183  reportMode = txGainPhMisMatchMonCfg.reportMode;
184  break;
185  case 11:
186  sprintf(&testname[0],"MON_TX0_BPM ");
187  reportMode = tx0BpmMonCfg.reportMode;
188  break;
189  case 12:
190  sprintf(&testname[0],"MON_TX1_BPM ");
191  reportMode = tx1BpmMonCfg.reportMode;
192  break;
193  case 13:
194  sprintf(&testname[0],"MON_TX2_BPM ");
195  reportMode = tx2BpmMonCfg.reportMode;
196  break;
197  case 14:
198  sprintf(&testname[0],"MON_SYNTHESIZER_FREQ ");
199  reportMode = synthFreqMonCfg.reportMode;
200  break;
201  case 15:
202  sprintf(&testname[0],"MON_EXTERN_ANALOG_SIG ");
203  reportMode = extAnaSigMonCfg.reportMode;
204  break;
205  case 16:
206  sprintf(&testname[0],"MON_TX0_INT_ANA_SIG ");
207  reportMode = tx0IntAnaSigMonCfg.reportMode;
208  break;
209  case 17:
210  sprintf(&testname[0],"MON_TX1_INT_ANA_SIG ");
211  reportMode = tx1IntAnaSigMonCfg.reportMode;
212  break;
213  case 18:
214  sprintf(&testname[0],"MON_TX2_INT_ANA_SIG ");
215  reportMode = tx2IntAnaSigMonCfg.reportMode;
216  break;
217  case 19:
218  sprintf(&testname[0],"MON_INT_RX_SIG ");
219  reportMode = rxIntAnaSigMonCfg.reportMode;
220  break;
221  case 20:
222  sprintf(&testname[0],"MON_INT_PMCLKLO_SIG ");
223  reportMode = pmClkLoIntAnaSigMonCfg.reportMode;
224  break;
225  case 21:
226  sprintf(&testname[0],"MON_INT_GPADC_SIG ");
227  reportMode = gpadcIntAnaSigMonCfg.reportMode;
228  break;
229  case 22:
230  sprintf(&testname[0],"MON_PLL_CONTROL_VOLT ");
231  reportMode = pllConVoltMonCfg.reportMode;
232  break;
233  case 23:
234  sprintf(&testname[0],"MON_DCC_CLOCK_FREQ ");
235  reportMode = dualClkCompMonCfg.reportMode;
236  break;
237  case 24:
238  sprintf(&testname[0],"MON_RX_IF_SATURATION ");
239  break;
240  case 25:
241  sprintf(&testname[0],"MON_RX_SIG_IMG_BAND ");
242  break;
243  case 26:
244  sprintf(&testname[0],"MON_RX_MIXER_INP_POWER");
245  reportMode = rxMixInpwrMonCfg.reportMode;
246  break;
247  default :
248  sprintf(&testname[0],"ERROR: UNDEFINED FEATURE");
249  break;
250  }
251 
252  if(i < MMWAVELINK_TEST_MAX_NUM_ANALOG_MON_REP)
253  {
254  /* This IF covers all analog monitors */
255  if(monAnaEnables.enMask & (1 << i))
256  {
257  //printf("checking %d\n",i);
258  if(reportMode == MON_REPORT_MODE_AT_FAILURE_ONLY)
259  {
260  /*Is this test configured to fail this monitoring feature?*/
261  if(gTestMiscCfg.failFeatureMask & (1 << i))
262  {
263  if(monAeCnt[i] != numRep)
264  {
265  System_printf("Error Monitoring feature %s: expected %d reports (induced failure). Received %d.\n",testname , numRep, monAeCnt[i]);
266  retVal = -1;
267  }
268  else
269  {
270  System_printf("[Debug]: Received %d reports for monitoring feature %s\n",monAeCnt[i], testname);
271  }
272  }
273  else
274  {
275  if(monAeCnt[i] != 0)
276  {
277  System_printf("Error Monitoring feature %s: expected 0 reports (reportMode = 1). Received %d.\n",
278  testname , monAeCnt[i]);
279  retVal = -1;
280  }
281  else
282  {
283  System_printf("[Debug]: Received Zero reports for monitoring feature %s\n", testname);
284  }
285  }
286  }
287  else
288  {
289  if(monAeCnt[i] != numRep)
290  {
291  System_printf("Error Monitoring feature %s: expected %d reports. Received %d.\n",testname , numRep, monAeCnt[i]);
292  retVal = -1;
293  }
294  else
295  {
296  System_printf("[Debug]: Received %d reports for monitoring feature %s\n",monAeCnt[i], testname);
297  }
298  }
299  }
300  else
301  {
302  //printf("skip %d\n",i);
303  /* This report was not enabled. */
304  if(monAeCnt[i] != 0)
305  {
306  System_printf("Error Analog Monitoring feature %s: expected zero reports. Received %d.\n", testname, monAeCnt[i]);
307  retVal = -1;
308  }
309  }
310  }
311  else if(i == MMWAVELINK_TEST_MON_REPORT_HEADER)
312  {
313  //printf("checking header %d\n",i);
314  /* This is the report header. Should only be sent when at least one report is enabled*/
315  if(monAnaEnables.enMask != 0)
316  {
317  if(monAeCnt[i] != numRep)
318  {
319  System_printf("Error report header: expected %d reports. Received %d.\n", numRep, monAeCnt[i]);
320  retVal = -1;
321  }
322  else
323  {
324  System_printf("[Debug]: Received %d report headers.\n",monAeCnt[i]);
325  }
326  }
327  else
328  {
329  /* No report was enabled. Should have not received any report header*/
330  if(monAeCnt[i] != 0)
331  {
332  System_printf("Error: report header received. But no report was enabled. Number of received reports %d\n", monAeCnt[i]);
333  retVal = -1;
334  }
335  }
336  }
337  else if(i == MMWAVELINK_TEST_MON_DIG_LATENT_FAULT)
338  {
339  /* This is digital latent fault. */
340  //printf("checking digital latent fault %d\n",i);
341  if(monDigEnables.enMask != 0)
342  {
343  if(monAeCnt[i] != gTestMiscCfg.numLatentFaultAfterFrameStop)
344  {
345  System_printf("Error Digital latent fault report: expected %d reports. Received %d.\n",
346  gTestMiscCfg.numLatentFaultAfterFrameStop, monAeCnt[i]);
347  retVal = -1;
348  }
349  else
350  {
351  System_printf("[Debug]: Received %d reports for Digital latent fault.\n",monAeCnt[i]);
352  }
353  }
354  else
355  {
356  /* No digital report was enabled. Should have not received any report*/
357  if(monAeCnt[i] != 0)
358  {
359  System_printf("Error: Digital latent fault report received. But no digital report was enabled. Number of received reports %d\n", monAeCnt[i]);
360  retVal = -1;
361  }
362  }
363  }
364  else if(i == MMWAVELINK_TEST_MON_DIG_PERIODIC_REP)
365  {
366  /* This is digital periodic report. */
367  //printf("checking digital periodic report %d\n",i);
368  if(monDigPeriodicCfg.periodicEnableMask != 0)
369  {
370  if(monAeCnt[i] != numRep)
371  {
372  System_printf("Error Digital periodic report: expected %d reports. Received %d.\n", numRep, monAeCnt[i]);
373  retVal = -1;
374  }
375  else
376  {
377  System_printf("[Debug]: Received %d reports for Digital periodic report.\n",monAeCnt[i]);
378  }
379  }
380  else
381  {
382  /* No digital report was enabled. Should have not received any report*/
383  if(monAeCnt[i] != 0)
384  {
385  System_printf("Error: Digital periodic report received. But no digital periodic report was enabled. Number of received reports %d\n", monAeCnt[i]);
386  retVal = -1;
387  }
388  }
389  }
390  else if(i == MMWAVELINK_TEST_CALIBRATION_REP)
391  {
392  /* This is periodic calibration report. */
393  System_printf("[Debug]: Received %d reports for periodic calibration.\n",monAeCnt[i]);
394  }
395  else
396  {
397  //printf("checking remaining counters %d\n",i);
398  /* This counter is not used, should not have any non-zero value. */
399  if(monAeCnt[i] != 0)
400  {
401  System_printf("Error: expected zero counter on position %d. Counter value is %d.\n", i, monAeCnt[i]);
402  retVal = -1;
403  }
404  }
405  }
406 
407  return retVal;
408 }

418 int32_t MmwaveLink_checkStatusFlag
419 (
420  char *verifyApiName,
421  rlUInt8_t reportMode,
422  rlUInt16_t statusFlags,
423  rlUInt16_t expectedStatusWithoutThresholdCheck,
424  rlUInt16_t expectedStatusWithThresholdCheck,
425  uint32_t monitoringFeatureIndex
426 )
427 {
428  if(reportMode == MON_REPORT_MODE_PERIODIC_WITHOUT_THRESHOLD_CHECK)
429  {
430  if(statusFlags != expectedStatusWithoutThresholdCheck)
431  {
432  monTestPassFlag = false;
433  System_printf("Error: %s rep->statusFlags = 0x%x. Expected value is 0x%x. Frame number %d.\n", verifyApiName,
434  statusFlags, expectedStatusWithoutThresholdCheck, gTestMCB.frameCnt);
435  return -1;
436  }
437  }
438  else if(reportMode == MON_REPORT_MODE_AT_FAILURE_ONLY)
439  {
440  /*Is this test configured to fail this monitoring feature?*/
441  if(gTestMiscCfg.failFeatureMask & (1 << monitoringFeatureIndex ))
442  {
443  /*Check if status flag matches the expected induced failure*/
444  if(statusFlags != gTestMiscCfg.failStatusFlag[monitoringFeatureIndex])
445  {
446  monTestPassFlag = false;
447  System_printf("Error: %s rep->statusFlags = 0x%x. Expected value is 0x%x (induced failure). Frame number %d.\n",
448  verifyApiName, statusFlags, gTestMiscCfg.failStatusFlag[monitoringFeatureIndex], gTestMCB.frameCnt);
449  return -1;
450  }
451  }
452  else
453  {
454 
455  System_printf("Error: %s Received report with rep->statusFlags = 0x%x. This is reportMode 1, no reports expected. Frame number %d.\n", verifyApiName,
456  statusFlags, gTestMCB.frameCnt);
457  return -1;
458  }
459  }
460  else if(reportMode == MON_REPORT_MODE_PERIODIC_WITH_THRESHOLD_CHECK)
461  {
462 
463  /*Is this test configured to fail this monitoring feature?*/
464  if(gTestMiscCfg.failFeatureMask & (1 << monitoringFeatureIndex ))
465  {
466  /*Check if status flag matches the expected induced failure*/
467  if(statusFlags != gTestMiscCfg.failStatusFlag[monitoringFeatureIndex])
468  {
469  monTestPassFlag = false;
470  System_printf("Error: %s rep->statusFlags = 0x%x. Expected value is 0x%x (induced failure). Frame number %d.\n",
471  verifyApiName, statusFlags, gTestMiscCfg.failStatusFlag[monitoringFeatureIndex], gTestMCB.frameCnt);
472  return -1;
473  }
474  }
475  else
476  {
477  if(statusFlags != expectedStatusWithThresholdCheck)
478  {
479  monTestPassFlag = false;
480  System_printf("Error: %s rep->statusFlags = 0x%x. Expected value is 0x%x. Frame number %d.\n",
481  verifyApiName, statusFlags, expectedStatusWithThresholdCheck, gTestMCB.frameCnt);
482  return -1;
483  }
484  }
485  }
486  else
487  {
488  monTestPassFlag = false;
489  System_printf("Error: %s reportMode = %d is invalid. Frame number %d.\n", verifyApiName, reportMode, gTestMCB.frameCnt);
490  return -1;
491  }
492  return 0;
493 }

503 void MmwaveLink_verifyTemperatureRep(rlMonTempReportData_t *rep)
504 {
505  uint32_t i;
506  int32_t retVal;
507 
508  monAeCnt[MMWAVELINK_TEST_MON_TEMP]++;
509 
510  #ifdef DEBUG_VERIFY
511  System_printf("MmwaveLink_verifyTemperatureRep\n");
512  System_printf("statusFlags = 0x%x\n",rep->statusFlags);
513  System_printf("errorCode = %d\n",rep->errorCode);
514  for(i=0; i<10; i++)
515  System_printf("tempValues[%d] = %d\n",i,rep->tempValues[i]);
516  System_printf("timeStamp = %d\n",rep->timeStamp);
517  #endif
518 
519  retVal = MmwaveLink_checkStatusFlag ("MmwaveLink_verifyTemperatureRep", tempMonCfg.reportMode,
520  rep->statusFlags, 0, 0x1F, MMWAVELINK_TEST_MON_TEMP);
521 
522  if(retVal < 0)
523  {
524  System_printf("MmwaveLink_verifyTemperatureRep\n");
525  System_printf("statusFlags = 0x%x\n",rep->statusFlags);
526  System_printf("errorCode = %d\n",rep->errorCode);
527  for(i=0; i<10; i++)
528  System_printf("tempValues[%d] = %d\n",i,rep->tempValues[i]);
529  System_printf("timeStamp = %d\n",rep->timeStamp);
530  }
531 
532  if(rep->errorCode != 0)
533  {
534  monTestPassFlag = false;
535  System_printf("Error MmwaveLink_verifyTemperatureRep: errorCode = %d. Expected value is zero.\n",rep->errorCode);
536  }
537 
538  for(i=0; i<10; i++)
539  {
540  if(rep->tempValues[i] > DFPTEST_MAX_TEMP)
541  {
542  monTestPassFlag = false;
543  System_printf("tempValues[%d] = %d exceeds the max allowed value %d.\n",i,rep->tempValues[i],DFPTEST_MAX_TEMP);
544  }
545  if(rep->tempValues[i] < DFPTEST_MIN_TEMP)
546  {
547  monTestPassFlag = false;
548  System_printf("tempValues[%d] = %d is lower than min allowed value %d.\n",i,rep->tempValues[i],DFPTEST_MIN_TEMP);
549  }
550  }
551 }

619  /* Bytes populated for each combination of RF and RX channel
620 
621  RF1 RF2 RF3 \n
622  RX0 1:0 9:8 17:16 \n
623  RX1 3:2 11:10 19:18 \n
